,Recommended,259570,33077077,Posted: 1 July,all,Adeptus Ineptus,"It's taken me a while to review this since starting to play; I guess because it's fairly different to the other survival games I've reviewed. Eden Star has a good, intuitive keymapping and crafting system but it's real focus is on destroying hives and defending outposts - much more combat based than other survival games. Multiplayer seems like it would be very rewarding as having fellow colonists to harvest resources and upkeep the base would make it easier to keep your outposts and make attacks against hives.A good feature of Eden Star is that you can adjust the world settings (such as player damage %, structure damage %, structure hit points, thirst & hunger depletion, enemy spawn rates etc.) and use Free Build mode if you want so that you can focus on base-building without having to repair anything or worry about dying. It's an enjoyable game so far and I'm looking forward to seeing the dev team add more to it! ****"
