,Recommended,259570,20193268,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,du = Tds - Pdv,"So to start of. For a pre-alpha game it's very impressive.Concept: The concept is very interesting. At times feels like a fpswith some satisfying weapons (currently pistol, SMG, Rifle, Sniper, Baton, Energy Baton)and then feels like a 3D mine craft.The build system is very similar to fallout 4 in terms of snapping objects etc..but atm, as it is pre-alpha, doesnt have content (basic structural components, 3 types of turret and a few utilities, power gen etc..)FPS: FPS wise it's pretty solid having been built with Unreal Engine 4.Weapons have satisfying models and sounds and the enemies are varied enough torequire different tactics not just spamming rifle. You can also upgrade youmining tool to project kinetic blasts for knock back and through upgradesadd furhter knock-back, damage, projected laser etc.. to make combat muchmore varied. Feels sort of like a fantasy RPS with both guns and magicks.Enemies: There are a select few differnt types of enemies that spawn at certain sites,destroying the hive while enemies attack is challanging and rewarding (rare ore telirium?)On a night they attack your base and if you don't take care of the hive the attacksbecome worse, sustaining damage to walls,defenses and your EDEN kit.Movement: I really like the parkour in this game. Very satisfying to be acble to scale rock faces withthe ability to actually reach ledges significatly higher than you.Mining: Mining is cool. Holding the right mouse strips ore deposits andtrees with a nice context menu telling u the compisition of different minearls.THe mining can also be upgraded to either be faster, reach futher or enhance combat by paralysing enemies andthen throwing them etc..Graphics: Very nice graphics as expected form unreal engine 4. Lighting is a bitodd for me (could just be me) but the light and dark areas can be too high contrast at times.However as pre-alpha this isn't something I would hold against the DEVS.Mulitplayer: Not done multiplayer yet but the devs have some pretty good looking guides forsetting up a server.Upgrading and construction: The upgrades and construction require certain minerals/oresas a base cost and some allow you to choose the aditional ore/mineral. This allowsyou to play stategically in what ores/minerals you have to spare etc..basic structures like walls etc. can be made using a select few, some way more common than othersbut the rarer minerals/ores add bonuses / debuffs to HP heat resistance etc... which is a nicetouch. Equipment wise upgrades for your mining tool, kinetic force, repair tools requires both specific minerals/oresand additional. Ammo is made at the Eden Kit so you have to work for your ammo, again a nice touch.Development: The devs seem very pasionate about this game and what they've promisedto include looks like this game could become very popular.Future prospects: Once more content is added, simple structures, utilties, defenses etc and more upgradesI think this game could be a real hit. I can forsee large multiplayer servers with factions etc..in a PVE environment. Differnt builds such as Heavy hitters, expert miners, expert navigators etc, crowd controllers..Bosses should be an interesting feature in terms of reward etc..Here are some of the features in dev at the time of this review:16km island, should be very interestingBoss like enemiesExplosive weapons - will like to see how much the ammo drains ur resourcesMore buildablesCreature creation - should be funVehicles - Yes please!and some features planned:more melee - would be cool to see upgradesupgradeable armour - very nice, shield upgrades? regen, damage etc...More utilities - not just power generatorscaves - would be awesome builing in a cave with a heavly fortified frontrobotic allies - customisable would be awesomeMy thoughts: Been a space age open world builder, I would like to see some advance structures andthe ability to change fine details etc.. no doubt someone will try and build a death star. Things like teleport stations so u can set up microbases in distant locations.Jump pads to cross chasms, surveying tools, maybe bots that go out to survey where goodsources of minerals are.Storage boxes are needed.More upgrade trees that allow characters to focus on one aspect. such as enhancing the fps elemnt,enhancing the ""magic"" elements, enhancing the melee elements. This could make boss battlessimilar to MMOs where each class can have a differnt input that complents others.Armour upgrades trees that can favor sotrage, defense, speed, parkour etc..Large muliplayer servers not just private ones (64 player+ ?)More trees etc...Game music etc..More minerals/ore types.Also with a game like this you need some way of keeping people interested. If I build everything why do I keep playing?By defeating bosses can I get new upgrades? Super rare ores to allow new upgrades?Prehaps require minerals/ores for a power source. Have a constant drain on the bae to encouragestocking more / upgrading eficieny.Overall I feel this game has real potential, based on what is already in this build.By buying pre-alpha you put money into something and the reward could be huge.p.s. wrote this article in a notepad editor and my spell check was giving me jip. Expect mistakes."
