,Recommended,259570,30772080,Posted: 27 March,all,Tampa Powers,"I have not played much yet, because I mostly went sandbox mode so I wouldn't get myself killed instantly. Some reviews here complain about the intro, but if you read the discussion forum you learn to switch to the experimental branch and to disable enemy spawn completely. Heck you can even turn damage off entirely, have not seen this many options in terms of AI in a game, means you can suit it exactly to your playstyle. Not to mention being able to change that on the fly while ingame.The game is very pretty and at that still runs quite well. My system of 5 years with an i7 990X and SLI GTX 780 cards had no issues running it at 60fps. So any new i5 and 900 to 1000 series cards will run it just fine.In terms of mechanics the whole pickup/mining takes a bit getting used to, but it is a nice change to pounding rocks with a pickaxe. I can only hope for future updates making resource gathering even easier and maybe automated too. Vehicles would probably also make a nice addition here, trying to get around the large game world can take some time, which is not a negative if you think about it.The base-building system, similar to the mining, takes a bit getting used to get things right where you want them, but it works and once you complete a large base I am sure it will look pretty cool.The fact multiplayer is already built in and continues to be improved is good to see, most games tend to neglect that part. I have not been able to test that yet, because it lacks a linux server version and somebody to play with :)Overall I can recommend this game, I played another space survival game the other day and had to refund that, cringed too hard at the mechanics, this was a refreshingly well made Early Access title and I can definitely see this beating some recently released AAA titles. For the price it already provided a nicer experience than what I have recently played in terms of space survival."
