76561198033755040,Recommended,259570,19978804,"Posted: 26 December, 2015",all,Cik,"7/10 for this EA Survival game [multiplayer, coop & single-player].Against the back-drop of several half-baked Early Access Survival games that aren't worth the asking price (except Dont Starve, Ark and Wurm Unlimited), this game certainly has a very unique and fresh spin on the genre, and it is very very actively supported by the devs, while it runs very smoothly.So, It feels to me like an open-world sci-fi survival game with a uniqe environmental tower-defence element to it.  Like Don't Starve, you take advantage of the day cycle to mine, scrounge, explore for resources, and build and adventure.  While at night, you defend your expanding base in a hostile environment that is also toxic at night, being a key component to the survival element.There is quite a ways to go with the content (redundancy of game-play and lack of wiki-game play development) , but having passed on other survival games, I have read, watched and feel this one is something special; at least can be more-so as necessary content is added.Again, my biggest con, which is understandable is content needs to be pushed into the game so it has more to offer than just repetitive building and base improving, such as more to explore, travel and value in defeating mobs.  For example, I just logged because of lack of wiki content while looking for material information that provides info on game-play content & mechanics was just irritating me too much."
