76561198020822530,Recommended,259570,25023136,"Posted: 19 August, 2016",all,The7thSaint,"While my overall experience didn't change much, I feel like this is one of the first EA games to actually do it right. This game is being built from the ground up, which means it doesn't and shouldn't have content for the sake of content. Too many games shove in content to keep players playing, but because they're so focused on content the games are a buggy mess. This game does it right, so props to the devs. When things are added to the game they're polished and mostly bug-free. Every single mechanic they've added feels like a finished part of a game in development. Too many EA games feel like something that won't ever get finished. This game constantly improves and feels like it's actually making progress towards a release, rather than something that is going to be EA forever.The amount of possibility right now is huge, this game can be more than just tower defense, more than just an action or open-world game. Depending on what's done this game could be something special. RNG loot, bosses, interesting and fun weapons, vehicles, different powers are all things that could be added to ultimately create an experience unlike any other I've seen and it excites me. Depending on what the devs decide to do this game could be truly huge.Solid. Polished. Professional. These are all words I'd use to describe this game and the devs. No, it's not finished. No, it doesn't have the content of a finished game, but that's a good thing because I want quality over quantity every day of the week. I'm looking forward to what happens next with this game.So far what I can say is: the combat is satisfying, the gathering doesn't feel like a chore and the building is fantastic. If you want to support some fantastic developers definitely give this game a try."
